\setdisplaytitle{Colimit of Cofinal Subdiagrams}

{{Cofinal-Subdiagram}}

Suppose there is a subdiagram inclusion \(\mathcal J \hookrightarrow \mathcal D\), or more generally just a functor. If this functor is cofinal, then the category cocones over \(\mathcal J\) and \(\mathcal D\) are equivalent.
